text: Whatawhata is a village in the region of Waikato, on the North Island of New Zealand. It had 2,475 people in 2013. It lies on the eastern side of the Waipa River. State Highways 23 and 39 cross each other at Whatawhata. Category:Villages Category:Settlements in Waikato Region Category:Waikato District
title: Whatawhata
